cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.LG

The paper deals with the construction of a 3D Morphable Model of the human head, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques for image reconstruction, graphics (GR) for modeling and rendering, multimedia (MM) for handling 3D data, human-computer interaction (HC) for parameterization, and machine learning (LG) for statistical modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.GR and cs.MM. The paper also involves some aspects of HCI and machine learning, which could place it in cs.HC and cs.LG, respectively.
